<TITLE> Committee seeks more time to file edn policy report </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 3 (bdnews24.com)A committee tasked with formulating a policy on the education system has sought a month's extension of the deadline to submit recommendations to the education ministry. "We officially asked for an extension on Sunday, though we informed the ministry of our intentions earlier," Quazi Kholiquzzaman Ahmed, co-chair of the committee and Bangladesh Economic Council chief, told bdnews24.com. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid announced formation of the National Education Policy Formulation Committee on April 8 headed by professor Kabir Chowdhury. The 16-member committee is tasked with introducing a modern education policy in line with guidelines prepared by the previous Awami League administration. The committee includes writer and science teacher Dr Muhammad Zafar Iqbal, vice-chancellor of the Open University Dr RIM Aminur Rashid and Jahangirnagar University's Prof Shaheen Kabir. Kholiquzzaman recently told bdnews24.com that a draft of the report suggested extending primary education up to class six by 2012. bd
